The paper focuses on learning disentangled representations from user behavior data in recommender systems. This involves using machine learning techniques to uncover and separate the latent factors that drive user decision-making processes. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and computer vision (cs.CV). However, given the focus on learning representations from user behavior data, we believe that cs.LG and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.CV.
